Title: Mean Field Approach to the Giant Wormhole Problem
Authors: A. Gamba, I. Kolokolov and M. Martellini
Comments: 10 pages, Latex
Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. D3 (1994) 421-430
\\
  We introduce a gaussian probability density for the space-time distribution
of wormholes, thus taking effectively into account wormhole interaction. Using
a mean-field approximation for the free energy, we show that giant wormholes
are probabilistically suppressed in a homogenous isotropic ``large'' universe.
